Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.75,0:01:36.30,Lyrics eng,,0,0,0,,To be reaching for the hope, I want to become a rainbow
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.43,0:01:46.44,Sign,,0,0,130,,{\blur1\b1\bord0\shad0\fade(400,400)\fs30\c&HEBDFD8&}Episode 3 \N\N\N\N\N\N\N{\fs60}Oddball
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.44,0:01:58.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You have... quite a cute-looking face.\NListen, please don't be mordacious.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.15,0:02:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the matter, Billy? \NWhat are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.49,0:02:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you be quiet for a minute, please?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.96,0:02:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,This fellow won't budge a bit!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.68,0:03:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I am definitely keeping you!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.61,0:03:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,My little sister Lucy-May was immediately \Nhead over heels for the cute animal from the tree top.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.78,0:03:44.29,Default,,0,0,0,,She decided to keep him no matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.29,0:03:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,On our way home, an aboriginal family \Nappeared out of nowhere in front of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.59,0:03:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Hands off!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.60,0:05:09.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy-May, chin up! \NYou'll have another chance to find that animal.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.81,0:05:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Sis, sis! Did you see it? \NThe way he was clinging{hugging} to that boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.11,0:05:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.21,0:05:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,What a truly adorable lad.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.02,0:05:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I will find him. \NAnd then no matter what anyone says, I am keeping him!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.08,0:05:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd keep him as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.88,0:05:28.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's about time we hurry back to mom. \NThis has already taken us indecently long.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.99,0:05:30.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Good call. Let's hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.63,0:05:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy-May!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.03,0:05:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You are carrying your bucket yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.83,0:05:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,My bad, my bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.51,0:05:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though you finally brought the water, \NI can but to scold you for how indecently long it took.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.64,0:05:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,We ran into aboriginals.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.71,0:05:52.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Aboriginals?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.91,0:05:54.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. A spear-armed ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.85,0:05:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Spear-armed? \NThen, did they do anything to you...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.69,0:06:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The aboriginal child plucked off me \Nthe cute animal we've caught earlier. {The aboriginal child took away for himself the cute animal we've caught earlier.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.36,0:06:08.70,Default,,0,0,0,,But that child also seemed to be caring for it. \NHe had a solid proof, so there was no room for objection.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.20,0:06:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly what type of animal?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.07,0:06:17.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what it is called, but it had a large nose, \Nthe cottonous{fluffy} fur and the cutest ever appearance!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.17,0:06:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you plan to use such an animal for, \Nhad you caught it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.34,0:06:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought I would keep it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.35,0:06:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Was bringing along your hamster Mosh \Nall the way from England not enough?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.76,0:06:30.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Even with your dad and mom pleading you not to!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.89,0:06:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to, because Mosh is a dear friend of mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.49,0:06:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is why Mosh is more than enough.\NTo adopt a yet another new animal would be ludicrous!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.13,0:06:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,When I told her so, \Nthis child wouldn't give an ear!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.40,0:06:46.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of question. \NIt's completely out of question, Lucy-May.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.70,0:06:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Having a squabble in raised voices, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.71,0:06:53.51,Default,,0,0,0,,How is your fever? \NReducing already?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.24,0:06:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, it seems to be gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.08,0:07:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It does. You are way colder than before. \NBut it's best that you don't wander around yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.52,0:07:04.99,Default,,0,0,0,,But everyone is in such a hustle. \NI'm the only one to be snoozing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.99,0:07:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Totally excusable for someone ill.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.29,0:07:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,But I want to be in any way helpful!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.92,0:07:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it's one more reason \Nto spend today resting peacefully. {Well, you should go have a sound sleep either way.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.50,0:07:17.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Because that is your mother's order.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.63,0:07:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.47,0:07:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Mosh!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.61,0:07:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder what such an animal even feeds on.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.31,0:07:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Nuts, probably. \NWhy else would it climb a tree?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.74,0:07:31.05,Default,,0,0,0,,That must be the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.05,0:07:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I will by any means catch that cute creature.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.15,0:07:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,When that happens, get along nicely, will you? {make good friends, okay?}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.49,0:07:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,My little sister Lucy-May \Nis really into extreme animals.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.52,0:07:46.29,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why she often knows the names \Nof animals she had never seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.70,0:07:52.47,Default,,0,0,0,,However, we didn't yet have any chance \Nto know about koalas, indigenous to Australia.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.47,0:07:58.27,Default,,0,0,0,,As it was revealed to us later, \Nkoala's menu consists exclusively of eucalyptus leaves.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.58,0:08:07.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, well, this tablecloth is permeated with mold.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.85,0:08:12.05,Default,,0,0,0,,No wonder since it spent three months \Ninside the humid ship underbelly.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.09,0:08:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that the trunk dad brought from the ship?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.23,0:08:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It is.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.96,0:08:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, dad and Ben are off to Adelaide?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.57,0:08:24.37,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.37,0:08:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are they, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.96,0:08:31.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Parker's tent collapsed for no particular reason, \Nso they are putting it back together with Ben.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.08,0:08:35.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, Ben. Get ready!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.71,0:08:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.61,0:08:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Heave-ho!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.25,0:08:44.79,Default,,0,0,0,,That should do it. \NAlright, now the other side.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.79,0:08:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.11,0:08:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you sure you don't want me to help?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.92,0:08:53.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It's fine if you just stop wobbling{loitering}  \Nand get seated out of the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.13,0:08:54.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.23,0:08:55.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright! Pull now, Ben!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.49,0:09:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, I'll take your word for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.64,0:09:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, yes. That's the way. \NI'll secure it on this end first!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.88,0:09:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,If you give it a thought, \NI'm rather a towny{This one can be derogatory but I can't see another appropriate informal adjective. Urban maybe?} type of man.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.34,0:09:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Which makes my ineptitude in tent hanging \Nperfectly justified.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.62,0:09:19.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess so.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.59,0:09:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Last night, when the tent poles gave in and it collapsed on me, \NI barely caught any shuteye!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.96,0:09:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You should have tended to it earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.13,0:09:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Good grief, I finally landed in Australia just to spend \Nthe initial night awake, propping up the tent poles!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.28,0:09:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,That will make a good memory for the future{later} you,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.24,0:09:44.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{who will be} living in a magnificent house.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.45,0:09:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Magnificent house?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.15,0:09:49.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Like the one you will build in the city of Adelaide.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.25,0:09:53.46,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I am not going to Adelaide. \NI will be doing trading{business} right here!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.22,0:09:54.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Here?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.99,0:10:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly. The flow of immigrants will be growing steadily. \NBefore long, a proper wharf will be arranged.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.46,0:10:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,A trading post will be indispensable then.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.97,0:10:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,No doubt, my business will rise and prosper here!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.74,0:10:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't know if it'll go this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.64,0:10:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it will definitely be so!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.95,0:10:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Ben! I untied the rope here to pull it once more. \NDo the same on your side!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.18,0:10:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.08,0:10:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Then tie a sturdy knot, this time for good.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.75,0:10:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,If we don't secure it tightly now, Mr. Parker \Nwill have another sleepless night of propping up the poles{, and we don't want it to happen}.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.33,0:10:37.97,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right, Ben! \NPlease secure it well{tightly}!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.40,0:10:43.71,Default,,0,0,0,,They're here, here!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.71,0:10:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like it is already almost done!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.52,0:11:03.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother!{Did they say bro back in 1800s?} Are you done already?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.76,0:11:06.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Did you come here for something? {Why did you come here?} {It sounds unreasonably blunt in literal form}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.59,0:11:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We came to see how you are doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.10,0:11:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't say nonsense. {Lit: You are speaking sassy.}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.20,0:11:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's true! Mr. Pettywell is also having dire times now, \Nbreaking his neck trying to fix a tent!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.50,0:11:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,When Mr. Pettywell's tent collapsed on him yesterday, \Nwe couldn't help bursting into cackle! {we started to laugh involuntairly!}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.34,0:11:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But Mr. Pettywell got so mad!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.24,0:11:23.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Naturally!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.31,0:11:29.05,Default,,0,0,0,,But Mr. Pettywell had such an ascended{dignified} look \Nwhile the tent was slowly descending{crumbling} upon his head...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.35,0:11:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Ben! You should stretch it harder!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.72,0:11:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.86,0:11:38.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.23,0:11:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I ask a small favor of young ladies?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.00,0:11:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.03,0:11:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Here is some lamb meat. \NI received it just recently. The freshest meat.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.37,0:11:51.29,Default,,0,0,0,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.33,0:11:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Today your side, namely your father, provided me service \Nof fixing my tent. This meat is my means of payment.{token of gratitude.} {He utilizes the formal stock brocker code, I believe 🤔}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.71,0:11:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.68,0:12:02.35,Default,,0,0,0,,This meat has not been salted yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.35,0:12:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course not! It's fresh meat!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.82,0:12:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate salted meat most of all! \NIt always has that weird smell.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.32,0:12:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,This meat is not mixed with any weird smells at all. \NNow, would you take it to your mother?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.30,0:12:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.83,0:12:19.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodbye!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.92,0:12:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't remember the last time we had fresh meat!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.43,0:12:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,All the meat they served on the ship was salted.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.80,0:12:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It must have been more than a hundred days ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.50,0:12:51.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.80,0:12:55.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Surely, you said your looong thanks to Mr. Parker?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.41,0:12:59.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you say it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.37,0:13:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I said it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.11,0:13:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,No, all you've said was "Goodbye", and nothing else!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.81,0:13:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Baloney! I said "Thank you!" \NIt was sis who clearly didn't say anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.92,0:13:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I probably expressed all due gratitude. \NIt's only natural when receiving goods from other people.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.96,0:13:18.09,Default,,0,0,0,,But sister positively never uttered any gratitude!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.09,0:13:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I can swear to God it was you who said nothing!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.40,0:13:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Give me a break, you two!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.74,0:13:29.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom, I'll leave it here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.47,0:13:32.54,Default,,0,0,0,,When your dad's party returns, we'll start cooking.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.98,0:13:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Could you go look after Tob, Clara?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.98,0:13:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.16,0:13:55.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, now, it's alright, Tob. \NWhat's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.10,0:13:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanna back home!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.76,0:13:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,This is our home now, Tob.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.30,0:14:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Wanna home!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.87,0:14:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to be patient while we're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.04,0:14:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We brought a marvelous prefabricated house \Nall the way from England to build it in the city of Adelaide.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.76,0:14:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody... Somebody catch that dog!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.22,0:14:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Kate!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.29,0:14:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Look out!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.46,0:14:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,My, that's bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.76,0:14:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody get that dog!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.63,0:14:25.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop right there!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.36,0:14:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Catch it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.46,0:14:32.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom! Hurry! Hurry up and catch that dog!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.33,0:14:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened, sis?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.00,0:14:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,There! See that dog? \NThat dog stole the meat you were paid with!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.55,0:14:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Heck!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.12,0:14:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Catch the damn thief dog!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.60,0:15:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Gotcha!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.91,0:15:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait! Wait!!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.22,0:15:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Catch it! \NCatch that damn dog!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.09,0:15:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, here!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.60,0:15:42.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not getting away! Take this!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.78,0:15:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, what's the matter, Happy? \NSomething hurt you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.95,0:16:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I say, what is this all about? What made you think \Nyou are entitled to be collectively bullying my dog?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.00,0:16:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That dog of yours is a burglar!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.00,0:16:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,,He is a burglar? You could make up a better slander. {I don't believe so.}\NPardon my bluntness, but this dog is better fed than you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.43,0:16:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, Happy?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.55,0:16:18.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Here! You can see for yourself! \NDog did this to our hard-earned meat...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.81,0:16:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,My, my, Happy, \Nyou feel like playing pranks today, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.64,0:16:26.51,Default,,0,0,0,,This transgresses any idea of prank, Mr. Pettywell! {This kind of prank is unforgivable, Mr. Pettywell!}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.68,0:16:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it you are trying to say, then? \NAre you implying I have to pay you the price for that meat?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.16,0:16:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,What price do you want for it, boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.99,0:16:39.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.30,0:16:48.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, Annie.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.47,0:16:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.97,0:16:53.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the three of you can return home.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.75,0:17:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Pettywell, that meat was priceless{of the greatest value} to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.46,0:17:14.10,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I'm willing to reimburse it. \NI'm not afraid to assume responsibility for my dog's tricks.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.10,0:17:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Even by paying for it, you won't earn our pardon!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.76,0:17:19.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't understand one bit what is it you want then!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.37,0:17:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you oblivious of the very concept of apology?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.20,0:17:26.27,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the logic behind me \Napologizing for dog's misbehavior?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.27,0:17:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Pettywell!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.38,0:17:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I have no words for you but... {It rather looks like he's about to say something R+ but Annie stops him. I don't see a way to put it in text.🤷}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.14,0:17:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Dear...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.98,0:17:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go home, dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.83,0:17:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We can no longer eat it, can we?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.40,0:17:54.04,Default,,0,0,0,,After such a long time, \Nwe were hoping to taste some genuine meat again.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.34,0:17:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it really inedible now?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.87,0:18:01.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's throw it away, mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.98,0:18:03.08,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.08,0:18:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,But what do we do with it, mom?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.38,0:18:08.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll wash it to edible. \NThe fresh meat is too precious to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.95,0:18:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,But to wash it... {But if you say wash...}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.15,0:18:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The sea is great for washing it. \NAfter that, we can eat it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.42,0:18:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I can wash it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.76,0:18:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I will go too!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.36,0:18:18.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I can do just fine alone!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.19,0:18:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I said I'll go, so I'll go!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.63,0:18:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll get in the way if you come!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.72,0:18:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Sis is a meanie!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.50,0:18:29.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Be careful now. \NBen, can you come along?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.17,0:18:29.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.77,0:18:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's fine, I can go alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.86,0:18:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Kate, that much washing should be enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.17,0:19:02.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It is so much smaller now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.54,0:19:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,When we just received it from Mr. Parker, \Nit was actually this big!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.21,0:19:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Fibber.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.41,0:19:12.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Who?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.51,0:19:13.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You, of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.81,0:19:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,What makes me a fibber?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.38,0:19:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,When we received it from Mr. Parker, \Nit was already this shrunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.02,0:19:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It was about that size. \NRight, bro?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.36,0:19:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It never was that big!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.36,0:19:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It was really \Nthis sizeable!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.83,0:19:29.33,Default,,0,0,0,,This inconsiderable!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.33,0:19:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Wrong! Big like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.96,0:19:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,That was more than enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.83,0:19:34.77,Default,,0,0,0,,What a fibber you are!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.77,0:19:36.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Sister is the only fibber here!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.34,0:19:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Except it's you!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.20,0:19:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.23,0:20:07.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Just how I remember it, \Nthe unsalted meat is delicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.77,0:20:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, the slice was so small, \NI barely grasped the taste.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.84,0:20:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it was totally delicious!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.25,0:20:19.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder, when{, if ever, } will be the next time \Nwe get to stuff our tummies with some fresh meat.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.71,0:20:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I don't believe it will take too long.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.28,0:20:26.89,Default,,0,0,0,,This country's lands are ample; the climate is favorable. \NIt fits stock breeding greatly.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.89,0:20:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,At the moment, I am devoted to building us a new farm. \NThough if we end up running a ranch, I won't mind either. {we might as well end up running a ranch.}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.36,0:20:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, my first step towards it \Nwould be going to Adelaide tomorrow{morning}.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.32,0:20:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I will pay a visit to general Light in the surveying office \Nto decide on{settle} our own plot as soon as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.24,0:20:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad, are you going there alone?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.31,0:20:51.31,Default,,0,0,0,,No, you are coming with me. If you memorize \Nthe road to Adelaide, it will come in handy later.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.75,0:20:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to go too!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.08,0:20:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Me too!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.38,0:20:57.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Not happening. \NThis time it's just Ben.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.02,0:21:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Our whole family is going to Adelaide soon anyhow. \NUntil then, you have to be patient.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.56,0:21:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't we see you off even part of the way? {We can turn back halfway.}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.72,0:21:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Unless you want to be credited with misbehavior! {I don't love children that don't listen well.}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.96,0:21:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,This means, after you return from Adelaide, we will unload our luggage and prefabricated house off the ship's belly?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.37,0:21:20.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The ship will be anchored for another 5 days... \NWell, there's really no point telling you that. {Well, you already know that better than anyone.}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.54,0:21:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,John would hardly omit that, talking to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.26,0:23:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it, Lucy-May?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.40,0:23:22.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.93,0:23:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Get back to sleep soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.60,0:23:32.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I am certainly catching it!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.10,0:24:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,When Billy grows up, \Nhe dreams of becoming an explorer.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.81,0:24:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So to promote it, we embarked on an expedition \Nto the other side of the cape.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.11,0:24:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time in Lucy-May of the Southern Rainbow: \NFirst Explorations. Join us again!
